The paper proposes a deep reinforcement learning approach to solve the packet classification problem, which involves optimizing for a global objective while navigating a tradeoff between computation and state complexity. This makes it likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates its solution on ClassBench, which is a dataset commonly used in the Computer Networks (cs.NI) sub-category. Finally, since the paper proposes a solution to a fundamental problem in computer networking, it could also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
